<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-453-810  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 453 810.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  July 1989 v26 n7 p49(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Security net. (data security)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Morris, Lewis C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Many deluded communications managers believe their information isinaccessible but indeed the integrity of communication systemsinvolving the use of cellular phones, microwave radio links orpublic or private networks may have already been compromised.andP;  Avast number of communications security systems are available, butmanagers must justify their purchase and implementation.andP;  Suchproducts must be physically secure, must not allow human access tosecret keys, must have a proven and tested cryptographicalgorithm, must have security equipment that is simple to operate,easy to install and never requires opening, and must haveequipment capable of interfacing with all types of protocols,synchronizing and clocking systems and a number of multiplexers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Data SecurityData CommunicationsEncryption.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>